references:
  - type: software
    authors:
      - alias: alchaincyf
    title: "nuwa-skill (女娲.skill)"
    url: "https://github.com/alchaincyf/nuwa-skill"
    license: "MIT"
    notes: >
      Methodological inspiration. Demonstrated that human cognitive
      frameworks can be distilled into runnable skills. Scholar-wendao
      redesigns this methodology specifically for academic humanities
      use, with different defaults (third-person analytical output vs.
      first-person role-play), different design philosophy (perspective
      skill vs. persona), and different epistemic boundary handling
      (5 honest-epistemics categories including the Polanyi tacit-knowledge
      problem, fossilization, public-vs-private filtering, biographical
      rhetoric contamination, and caricaturization risk).
